To install Bio::PrimerDesigner, run the following commands:

  $ perl Build.PL
  $ ./Build
  $ ./Build test
  $ su
  # ./Build install

To learn which arguments Build.PL accepts, run the following command:

  $ perl Build.PL [-h|--help]

NOTE: For local installations, make sure you have installed the binary 
executables for your OS for primer3 and e-PCR

  e-PCR  : http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sutils/e-pcr/
  primer3: http://primer3.sourceforge.net

Included are two scripts:

  primer_designer.cgi: Installed on remote linux/unix webserver to
    provide access to thr primer3 and e-PCR binaries.  Requires a
    server-side installation of Bio::PrimerDesigner

  primer_designer: Script to demonstrate Bio::PrimerDesigner functions

Google Code project home page:

  http://code.google.com/p/bio-primer-designer/

CPAN home page:

  http://search.cpan.org/dist/Bio-PrimerDesigner/

If you have problems, please contact the author:

  Sheldon McKay <mckays@cshl.edu>
